Interface StackOfIntegerInterface

public interface StackOfIntegerInterface
Interface for a stack of Integer objects.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void clear()
    Pops all elements off this stack, if any exist.
    boolean isEmpty()
    Returns true if this stack is empty, returns false otherwise.
    java.lang.Integer peek()
    Returns, but does not remove, the element at the top of the stack.
    java.lang.Integer pop()
    Removes and returns the element on the top of the stack.
    void push​(java.lang.Integer e)
    Adds the given element to the top of the stack.
    int size()
    Returns the number of elements in this stack.
    java.lang.String toString()
    Returns a string containing each element in this stack, separated by commas, enclosed in square brackets, with TOS indicated.

      java.lang.String toString()
      Returns a string containing each element in this stack, separated by commas, enclosed in square brackets, with TOS indicated. The top of the stack is shown to the left and indicated with "TOS" plus a single space. For example: "TOS [3, 2, 1]"
      Overrides:
